<Heading HeadingSize="HeadingSize.H3">Usage</Heading>

<Paragraph>Add BlazorStyled to <code>Startup.cs</code>. Setting <code>isDevelopment</code> to "true" will cause BlazorStyled to write the styles as text nodes in a style tag. 
    This allows the styles to be edited in the browser dev tools. Setting <code>isDevelopment</code> to "false" (the default if not specified) will cause BlazorStyled to write styles
    using <code>CSSStyle​Sheet​.insert​Rule()</code> which is faster but not editable in the browser dev tools (note the documentation site is set to development mode):
    </Paragraph>

<CodeBlock>
public void ConfigureServices(IServiceCollection services)
{
    services.AddBlazorStyled(isDevelopment: true);
}
</CodeBlock>

<Paragraph>Add the reference to the package to your <code>_Imports.razor</code> file:</Paragraph>

<CodeBlock>
@@using BlazorStyled
</CodeBlock>

<Paragraph>Finally, inject <code>IStyled</code> into your component:</Paragraph>

<CodeBlock>
@@inject IStyled Styled
</CodeBlock>